<div id="review_497512593" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/497512593" />
    <a title="Donna Crupi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5964458-donna-crupi"><img alt="Donna Crupi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1334068283p2/5964458.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/497512593?book_show_action=true">Jan 06, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donna Crupi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donna Crupi" href="/user/show/5964458-donna-crupi">Donna Crupi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451210463" href="/book/show/92371.Lie_Down_with_Lions">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer497512593" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10987464006461483079">My first Ken Follett novel. Wow! I think I was in high school on vacation with friends. I had no idea the power of a great story. Of the impact it could have on me. Of the connection I could feel to struggles of the characters and my desire to be one of those characters!<br/><br/>In hindsight, I don&apos;t want to know if this was a great book or not. I want to remember the man and woman struggling to cross the mountains in Afghanistan to get to freedom. I want to remember the passion I had never, never known </span>
  <span id="freeText10987464006461483079" style="display:none">My first Ken Follett novel. Wow! I think I was in high school on vacation with friends. I had no idea the power of a great story. Of the impact it could have on me. Of the connection I could feel to struggles of the characters and my desire to be one of those characters!<br /><br />In hindsight, I don't want to know if this was a great book or not. I want to remember the man and woman struggling to cross the mountains in Afghanistan to get to freedom. I want to remember the passion I had never, never known of before. I want to remember how I felt turning the pages with the danger and sexual desire of the couple as they moved onward.<br /><br />If you've read Follett, you know what he can do with characters and a story and an amazing backdrop. This book taught me.<br /><br />I highly recommend!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10987464006461483079" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


