        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1012087602" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12549923169204453038">Perhaps not the greatest book, but it was the first I ever learned of Ahmad Shah Masood, the legendary mujaheddin commander known as the &quot;Lion of Panjshir,&quot; and generally considered the all-around &quot;best hope for the future of Afghanistan&quot; - right up until he Osama bin Laden blew him up on Sept 9, 2001 as part of the whole 9/11 attack.* <br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1607290077i/30483733._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Interestingly, this was published just two years before &quot;Rambo III&quot; came out; back when supplying stingers to the proto-Taliban still seemed like a good idea, whe</span>
  <span id="freeText12549923169204453038" style="display:none">Perhaps not the greatest book, but it was the first I ever learned of Ahmad Shah Masood, the legendary mujaheddin commander known as the "Lion of Panjshir," and generally considered the all-around "best hope for the future of Afghanistan" - right up until he Osama bin Laden blew him up on Sept 9, 2001 as part of the whole 9/11 attack.* <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1607290077i/30483733._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Interestingly, this was published just two years before "Rambo III" came out; back when supplying stingers to the proto-Taliban still seemed like a good idea, when the whole Cold War was winding down and the term "War on Terror" hadn't even been invented yet. <br><i><br>* A lifelong guerilla leader, Masood survived over two decades of assassination attempts before being finally killed in during an interview at his own headquarters, when the fake "reporters" set off a bomb hidden in their camera. With American troops </i>still<i> on the ground in Afghanistan, I often wonder how different the past twenty years could have been, if only...</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="12549923169204453038" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

